# Minimal Panel UI

Design this app as a clean local desktop CRM panel. Prefer calm, professional surfaces over decorative UI.

## Visual language

- Use neutral page background `#F4F5F7` and white surfaces
- Prefer 1px borders (`AppUiTokens.border`) over shadows and elevation
- Keep brand accent (`ColorName.primary`) for primary actions and selected states only
- Use soft accent background (`AppUiTokens.accentSoft`) for selected nav / icon badges
- Typography: short titles, muted secondary text, no excessive bolding

## Layout

- Auth pages: centered card via `AuthPageScaffold` + `PanelSurface`
- Dashboard: light sidebar + top bar + bordered content panel
- Spacing scale: 8 / 12 / 16 / 24 / 32 from `AppUiTokens`
- Border radius: 8 (inputs), 12–16 (cards/panels)

## Responsive (required)

Every screen and shared widget must be responsive. Do not ship fixed desktop-only layouts.

- App root already uses `CustomResponsive.build` + `responsive_framework` breakpoints:
  - MOBILE: 0–450
  - TABLET: 451–800
  - DESKTOP: 801–1920
  - 4K: 1921+
- Use `ResponsiveBreakpoints.of(context)` or `LayoutBuilder` to adapt layout, not hard-coded widths
- Prefer flexible layouts: `Expanded`, `Flexible`, `ConstrainedBox`, `SingleChildScrollView`, `Wrap`
- Auth cards: keep `maxWidth` constraints; reduce horizontal padding on small screens
- Dashboard shell:
  - Desktop/tablet: sidebar + content
  - Mobile/narrow: collapse sidebar (drawer or top nav), stack content vertically
- Typography: use theme text styles; scale via existing `getResponsiveTextTheme` when needed
- Touch targets: minimum ~44px height on interactive controls
- Test layouts at narrow (~390), tablet (~768) and desktop (~1280+) widths before finishing UI work

```dart
// Good
LayoutBuilder(
  builder: (context, constraints) {
    final isCompact = constraints.maxWidth < 800;
    return isCompact ? _MobileLayout() : _DesktopLayout();
  },
);

// Avoid
SizedBox(width: 1200, child: ...); // fixed layout
```

## Components

Reuse shared widgets before creating page-specific styling:

- `AuthPageScaffold`, `PanelSurface`
- `PanelTextField`, `PanelPrimaryButton`, `PanelMessage`

Do not duplicate colors or spacing inline when a token/widget exists.

## Avoid

- `Get.snackbar`, `ScaffoldMessenger` snackbars, toast overlays for errors/success on desktop
- Heavy card elevation, gradients, glassmorphism
- Dark full-color sidebars unless explicitly requested
- Random `Colors.*` usage outside semantic/error states
- Crowded forms, oversized icons, decorative badges
- Inline auth/business logic in widgets

## Feedback (desktop)

- Show validation and auth errors inline with `PanelMessage` or form-level text
- Do not use snackbars/toasts; they behave poorly on desktop Flutter apps
- Success states: navigate to the next screen or update inline UI; no popup toast

## Pointer cursor (desktop)

All clickable UI must show `SystemMouseCursors.click` on hover.

- Configure button themes via `AppInteractiveTheme` in `custom_light_theme.dart`
- For custom taps (`InkWell`, `GestureDetector`), set `mouseCursor: SystemMouseCursors.click`
- Disabled controls use `SystemMouseCursors.basic`
- Do not leave default arrow cursor on buttons, links, sidebar items, or icon actions

## Example

```dart
// Good
return AuthPageScaffold(
  title: 'Ok Teknik Metal CRM',
  subtitle: 'Güvenli masaüstü giriş',
  child: PanelPrimaryButton(label: 'Giriş Yap', onPressed: controller.login),
);

// Avoid
return Card(elevation: 8, child: ...);
```
